@merlimat, We saw that the size of the folder `/data/ledgers/current/locations` was 25 GB before and 3 GB after rebuilding the index. Do you know if there is any setting that could prevent this growing? Or updating bookies and rocksdb is the only fix?

Beyond that, do you think that 3 GB for a clean index is ok? Our bookies currently have 4 GB for blockCacheSize.

Thanks!

@merlimat could you help us with this please?
We're seeing the the locations folder tends to grow a lot and after rebuilding the index, the size drops a lot. Could it be that rocksdb is not deleting the data? Or that it's not compacting frequently?

Is there any settings to tweak this?

